**[1867, 02] Ms.A.1.2.35.7A**

Pugh to RDW. Urges him to come to the U.S. “You of course see the
Standard as your sympathies are with its continuance.” Mentions seeing
Anthony and Stanton, and says Webb must remember “Mrs. Stanton, the
young bride in ’40 when we were all in London town. … You ask me of old
friends. The upheaving of the country, as well as the inevitable course
of time have swept apart many of the associates of former years, not
that we love one another less, but other interests & other duties press
their claims.” Gives what news she knows about MWC, Mary Grew, Abby
Kimber.


